Package: duckbotos-lm-studio
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 curl,
 systemd
Pre-Depends: bash (>= 4.0)
Description: DuckBotOS LM Studio — first-class local model provider
 Installs LM Studio as a first-class local model provider for DuckBotOS.
 LM Studio provides an OpenAI-compatible REST API on port 1234 for
 local LLM inference with GPU acceleration (CUDA/ROCm when available).
 .
 Installed path: ~/.lmstudio/ (user home, no root required)
 Binary: ~/.lmstudio/bin/llmster (headless server)
 CLI:      ~/.lmstudio/bin/lms      (model management)
 API:      http://127.0.0.1:1234/v1  (OpenAI-compatible)
 .
 JIT model loading is enabled by default — models are loaded on first
 inference request and stay in memory until unloaded or system restart.
 .
 Systemd unit: lmstudio.service (user-level, started on login)
 Config:     ~/.lmstudio/lmstudio.json
 Models dir: ~/.lmstudio/models/
 .
 GPU memory limits are set via /etc/security/limits.d/lmstudio.conf
 to allow larger context models to stay loaded in memory.
 .
 Port: 1234 (localhost only, no remote access by default)
